How will kubelet schedule a pod on its nodeâ“

Static pods are special type of pods managed directly by the kubelet on each node rather than through the Kubernetes API server ðŸ’» .

Unlike ðŸš«deployments and replica sets the Kubernetes scheduler does not manage static pods.
Configuration files ðŸ—ƒ  for static pods are placed directly on the node's file system, and the kubelet watches ðŸ‘€ these files for creation of pod and any changes in these will be automatically updated.

Static pods can only be deleted âŽ by modifying the files from the nodes manifest folder ðŸ“‚ .

Examples: ApiServer, ETCD, Kube-scheduler, controller-manager, etc............

Managing Static Pods ðŸ‘¨ðŸ’¼ :
ðŸ”¹SSH into Node where static pod is defined.
ðŸ”¹To view pods >> docker ps
ðŸ”¹Modify(edit/create) the YAML file for static pod.
ðŸ”¹To stop the pod, remove or modify the file directly from the node.
ðŸ”¹Default location is "/etc/kubernetes/manifests/" . We can place the pod YAML in the directory, and kubelet will pick it for scheduling.

To find the path of the directoryðŸ“‚ holding the static pods definition file 
>> cat var/lib/kubelet/config.yaml 
(Here path will be defined as staticPodPath: <Path>)
